<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,1086,2011]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1842,1867]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1966" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[674,933,1842,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidus">
<emphasis box="[674,784,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">A. bifidus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[792,933,1842,1867]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" refId="ref280374" refString="Evans, H. E. (1966) A revision of the genus Anisepyris Kieffer (Hymenoptera. Bethylidae). Studia Entomologica, 9, 1 - 120." type="journal article">Evans, 1966</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by having the posterior hypopygeal margin with a distinctly slender region; and the genitalia with the paramere having its ventral arm very wide and its apex truncate and not incurved, and the dorsal arm short, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[883,995,1914,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidus">
<emphasis box="[883,995,1914,1939]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">A. bifidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the posterior hypopygeal margin without a distinctly slender region; and the genitalia with the paramere having its ventral arm longer and wider than the ventral arm, with its apical margin incurved, and its dorsal arm long.
</paragraph>
